      "is_accepted": false,
      "score": 0,
      "last_activity_date": 1728683928,
      "creation_date": 1728683928,
      "answer_id": 79079810,
      "question_id": 10604298,
      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<p>I just want to add a specific edge case where certain components are preferable to be configured as @Bean's rather than @Component, @Service</p>\n<p>One such scenario is when doing @WebMvcTest for testing authentication.\nBecause @WebMvcTest auto configures Spring security if it is found on the classpath, but then because certain custom beans declared as @Service, will not be picked up by component scanning.</p>\n<p>If I declare it as a @Bean in a config file, it can just be imported inside and used around</p>\n"
    }
